messages.message:
Before I get ahead of myself, I have a meeting being setup with Bing Maps (vs OpenStreet Maps).  @Karthik S I think this would be great for global trade finance.

These are meetings setup when I was in Seattle so want to make sure I get the right people on them. Anyone else want to be involved
It'd be great to see what Bing maps can offer. Will definitely be helpful in Global trade finance. Keeping @Aaron Vontell in the loop

we looked extensively at bing maps vs google maps vs here vs mapbox at blend, i can't remember the conclusion but the price differences were huge
(ended up doing nothing and stuck with google since thats what we originally integrated with)
We have the ability to try before we buy. Once we want to buy we can work out pricing. Not to get reliant on it but want to figure out if its worth negotiating for
What would be very useful for us is given a stream of text, if they provide some form of address parsing functionality. We can integrate this to @Aaron Vontell's Global Address work.
When I was there, they were working on integrating: Weather, Traffic, Drone Data, Satellite Data, and so much more... it'll be fun to see how it does
Larger product question is when does: Map's, Translate, Handwriting, etc become app's on the platform vs.... Lens or Sequencer
